Description: Outlook.com is an email service operated by Microsoft. It was founded in 1996 as Hotmail, re-launched as MSN Hotmail after Microsoft acquired it in 1997, then re-launched as Outlook.com in 2013.
Gmail is an email service developed for limited release in 2004 and fully launched in 2009 by Google.
Yahoo! Mail is a web-based email service operated by Verizon Media. It was launched in 1997.
Daum Mail is the main email service of South Korean internet company Kakao. It was established in 2014 following the merger of Daum Communications and Kakao.
Yandex.Mail is an email service offered by the Russian company Yandex N.V.
Mail.Ru is an email service started in 1998 by the Russian internet company Mail.Ru.
